              <m>f(1)</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>f(\sqrt{3}+i)</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>f(1+i\sqrt{3})</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>f(3+4i)</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Is <m>f</m> a one-to-one function?
              Why or why not?
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="x2_1_7">
      <p>
        For <m>z \ne 0</m>, let <m>f(z) =\ln r+i\theta</m>,
        where <m>r=|z|</m>, and <m>\theta =\mathrm{Arg}\,z</m>.
